<br>
What I referred to was the last few times a guild jumped on someone else's plans, it was accompanied by rants about how there are too many planar guilds, and all the 50+ level folks are getting bottlenecked on planar drops for their epics.<br>
<br>
1. Server too old? Well in relation to solusek ro, where I came from..no it isnt, but EQ is too damn easy with Kunark and velious in it. People level too fast, therefore, a split would help.<br>
<br>
2. Epic system is flawed. (Flawed is a bit strong a word perhaps). There are a half dozen guilds that hit planar level in the past 4-8 weeks. There are also the guilds that wouldnt touch the planes of hate/fear were it not for epic drops being found there. So instead of 6 guilds going up, we have about 11. That is a flaw. It forces over competition, and delays the schedules of hundreds of people.<br>
<br>
3. Cambridge dictionary: Policy (plan) :a set of ideas or a plan of what to do in particular situations that has been agreed officially by a group of people, a business organization, a government or a political party.<br>
The players of Druzzil Ro are mostly adult, and therefore saw an impediment to fun. They created the dro site including the raid board, and others created the IGB. Both of these help the player base FAR more than some lame PNP policy set by verant.  <p><br><b>Lilhaer Blackdagger</b>
